Coronavirus in the US: Latest COVID-19 news and case counts


By

Live Science Staff 





The U.S. nears the grim milestone of 100,000 deaths related to COVID-19.
Sun unleashes biggest flare since 2017. Is our star waking up?

You'd be, too, when 18 years of work pays off like this.

By

Jeanna Bryner
